[137.758577, "i", "cat > BUGFIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\n# Pipeline Checkpoint/Resume Bug Fixes\n\n## Bugs Found and Fixed\n\n### Bug 1: Checkpoint file not properly flushed to disk\n**Problem:** The original code used `json.dump({'last_line': batch_num}, open('.checkpoint', 'w'))` without a context manager or explicit flush. This meant the checkpoint data could remain in the buffer and not be written to disk before a crash.\n\n**Fix:** Use proper context manager with explicit flush and fsync:\n```python\nwith open('.checkpoint', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump({'last_line': last_line}, f)\n    f.flush()\n    os.fsync(f.fileno())  # Ensure it's written to disk\n```\n\n### Bug 2: Checkpoint saved batch number but treated it as line number\n**Problem:** The checkpoint saved `batch_num` (0, 1, 2...) with the key 'last_line', then on resume it skipped that many individual lines instead of batches. This caused massive confusion:\n- After processing 1 batch (1000 lines), it saved batch_num=1\n- On resume, it would skip only 1 line and reprocess lines 2-1000\n\n**F"]
[137.758695, "i", "ix:** Track and save the actual line number processed:\n```python\nline_num = i + 1  # Track the last line we've read\nif len(batch) >= BATCH_SIZE:\n    process_batch(conn, batch)\n    save_checkpoint(line_num)  # Save actual line number\n```\n\n### Bug 3: INSERT OR REPLACE overwrites data instead of accumulating\n**Problem:** The SQL used `INSERT OR REPLACE` which completely replaces existing rows. When resuming, this would overwrite previous aggregations instead of adding to them, causing data loss.\n\n**Fix:** Use INSERT ... ON CONFLICT to accumulate values:\n```python\nconn.execute('''\n    INSERT INTO summary (category, total_value, count) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n    ON CONFLICT(category) DO UPDATE SET\n        total_value = total_value + excluded.total_value,\n        count = count + excluded.count\n''', (cat, data['total'], data['count']))\n```\n\n### Bug 4: No commit after each batch\n**Problem:** Database changes were only committed at the end, so a crash would lose all progress.\n\n**Fix:** Commit after each batch:\n```python\ndef"]
[137.758742, "i", " process_batch(conn, batch):\n    # ... process data ...\n    conn.commit()  # Commit after each batch\n```\n\n## Test Results\n\n✓ Single interruption and resume: PASSED (50,000 records, no duplication)\n✓ Multiple interruptions and resume: PASSED (50,000 records, no duplication)\n✓ Works with run.sh script: PASSED\n\n## Summary\n\nThe checkpoint mechanism now correctly:\n1. Persists checkpoint data to disk immediately (survives crashes)\n2. Tracks actual line numbers (not batch numbers)\n3. Accumulates data on resume (doesn't overwrite)\n4. Commits after each batch (progress is saved)\nEOF\n"]
[137.758753, "o", "cat > BUGFIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[137.758782, "o", " process_batch(conn, batch):\r\n    # ... process data ...\r\n    conn.commit()  # Commit after each batch\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Test Results\r\n\r\n✓ Single interruption and resume: PASSED (50,000 record"]
[137.75883, "o", "s, no duplication)\r\n✓ Multiple interruptions and resume: PASSED (50,000 records, no duplication)\r\n✓ Works with run.sh script: PASSED\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nThe checkpoint mechanism now correctly:\r\n1. Persists checkpoint data to disk"]
[137.758876, "o", " immediately (survives crashes)\r\n2. Tracks actual line numbers (not batch numbers)\r\n3. Accumulates data on resume (doesn't overwrite)\r\n4. Commits after each batch (progress is s"]
